SALMON MIGRATION INFOGRAPHIC


Description

This infographic illustrates the lifecycle of the Pacific Chinook "King" Salmon along the Columbia River. The product includes research, pictures, statistics, charts, and maps. Two custom maps were created for the dams on the Columbia river with the seasonal migration tributaries and a proportional symbol showing the salmon counts recorded at the dams for each season.


Skills

Cartography | Proportional Symbols


Software/Programming

Adobe Illustrator | Adobe Photoshop | ArcGIS Desktop | Microsoft Excel

BIKE THE GREAT LAKES PROFESSIONAL CARTOGRAPHY


Description

This map displays a conceptual 21-stage bike race beginning in Thunder Bay, Ontario and finishing in Quebec City, Quebec. It is broken out into 23 days averaging nearly 100 miles per day with two rest days. The map features a custom shaded relief and hillshade background. Other supporting data and layers have been added to the map including pictures, text, scale bar, and an elevation profile.


Skills

Cartography | Digital Elevation Models | Land Cover


Software/Programming

Adobe Illustrator | Adobe Photoshop | ArcGIS Desktop | Google Earth

WISCONSIN SPATIAL ANALYSIS OF NITRATE CONCENTRATIONS AND CANCER RATES


Description

This product features interactive spatial analysis to review the possible link between nitrate concentrations and cancer rates. Spatial interpolation can be compared by changing the K-value and cell size. The linear regression can be computed after the new interpolation layer has been created.


Skills

Choropleth | GeoJSON/TopoJSON | Linear Regression | Spatial Interpolation


Software/Programming

ArcGIS | CSS | HTML | JavaScript - Bootstrap, JQuery, Leaflet, Simple Statistics, Turf

ACADIA NATIONAL PARK GIS APPLICATION


Description

This product is a full web page configured with a sidebar containing eight tabs. The main map displays all the points of interest in Acadia National Park. Hiking paths can be filtered with the dropdown selection. There are also tools to select your location and finds features in your proximity. The app also has a customer survey which then updates input on the map. On the backend there are several layers feeding the app from a PostgreSQL database.


Skills

Attribute Filter | GeoJSON/TopoJSON | Proximity Search | Tooltips | User Survey


Software/Programming

CARTO | CARTO Builder | CSS | HTML | JavaScript - Bootstrap, JQuery, Leaflet | Mapbox | PostgreSQL

Career Highlights

  • Experienced in managing a multitude of tasks simultaneously, solving complex problems and arriving at effective solutions in a fast paced, time-sensitive environment.
  • Exceptional communication and organizational skills gained from an extensive background of planning, exercises and real world operations.


Education

Experience

Department of Veterans Affairs (Virtual) - June 2020 - Present

  • Serve as the GIS Coordinator to the VHA Support Services Center (VSSC).
  • Create healthcare related geospatial products for customers as needed.
  • Assist in the maintenance of the ArcGIS Enterprise instance.
  • Publish and maintain spatial data used in web applications and data analytics software.


Federal Emergency Management Agency (Chicago, IL) - September 2016 – June 2020

  • Serve as the Regional Geospatial Coordinator (RGC) for FEMA Region 5 covering Illinois, Indiana, Ohio, Michigan, Minnesota and Wisconsin.
  • Produce and supervise production of Geographic Information Systems (GIS) static maps and interactive online maps to FEMA, other federal agencies, states and local governments.
  • Maintain Region 5 ArcGIS Server’s data and services.
  • Leverage FEMA’s GeoPlatform ArcGIS Online account and DHS’ Geospatial Information Infrastructure (GII) ArcGIS Portal to create custom web maps and applications for planning and disaster relief operations.
  • Provide expertise to assist FEMA HQ with the development of a new cloud-based mapping platform and remote sensing prioritized collection strategy.
  • Apply weather forecasts, census demographics and critical infrastructure/key resources data toprovide situational awareness to senior leadership and staff.
  • Support regional planning efforts with geospatial response support for severe weather, earthquakes, power outages and national special security events.

United States Army (Alexandria, VA) - June 2010 – September 2016

  • Managed the GIS and imagery production of a diverse team including active duty Army personnel, federal civilians and contractors.
  • Trained and mentored co-workers in the concepts of GIS, remote sensing phenomenology and collection management procedures.
  • Standardized production workflows and instilled a thorough quality control/assurance process.
  • Created geospatial products using Esri ArcGIS desktop software, ArcSDE and ArcGIS Server.
  • Routinely used Remote View, SOCET GXP and ENVI to process and exploit imagery.
  • Deployed to Germany and Iraq in support of special operations task forces.


National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency (Springfield, VA) - April 2009 – June 2010

  • Produced visualization graphics and represented Source at NGA daily operations-intelligence briefs.
  • Briefed source strategies to the director, executive staff and visiting VIPs with little to no supervision.
  • Developed innovative techniques and models to better represent NTM, OPIR, commercial and airborne collection.
  • Utilized RMS and GIMS tools to conduct advance research on complex collection issues.
  • Coordinated airborne strategies with multiple agencies and COCOMs to help complement NTM collection.
  • Responded to many high current issues and environmental disasters while coordinating with other entities of the intelligence community.


DELEX Systems Inc. (Washington D.C.) - August 2008 – April 2009

  • Produced geospatial intelligence products in support of deploying Naval Riverine Squadrons.
  • Applied imagery analysis techniques to exploit change detection and trend analysis.
  • Edited, attributed and created vector datasets from imagery based data extraction.
  • Created standard operating procedures for map production and data management and assisted in the design of new geospatial templates and database architecture.


United States Marine Corps (Active Duty/Multiple Locations) - October 2003 – October 2008

  • Served as Topographic NCOIC in conventional military, naval expeditionary and special operations units throughout active duty career with multiple deployments to Guam, South Korea, Thailand, Philippines and Afghanistan.
  • Produced custom geospatial products to include helicopter landing zones, beach landings, cross-country mobility, soil, vegetation, route and slope studies.
  • Provided daily GEOINT analysis, crisis support and target packages (GRGs and 3D perspective views) to MARSOC special reconnaissance and direct action targeting efforts.

Hello! I am Jonathan Hansel and currently live in Chicago, IL. I have been married for almost 14 years and also have a German Shepherd dog.


In my spare time I love the outdoors... whether its trail running, hiking or fishing I love just getting fresh air.


I have served in the U.S. Marine Corps and traveled the world. I hold a Bachelor of Science in Geography from George Mason University in Fairfax, VA and currently working on my Master of Science in GIS and Web Programming at the University of Wisconsin - Madison.


Please feel free to contact me at jhansel@wisc.edu. Thanks for stopping by!
